      "content": "While the sensation is largely unavoidable during intense anaerobic exercise, there are some strategies to help manage the pain. Breathing techniques, such as deep, diaphragmatic breathing, can help reduce lactic acid production and alleviate the pain. Additionally, cardiac output manipulation, such as increasing ulnar artery compression, can help buffer lactic acid and delay its accumulation. Some athletes also use techniques like median nerve compression, or specific stretching and injection of anti-inflammatory substances directly into the affected area, to reduce pain in mid-sprint.",
